5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 513, L.D. 806, “An Act to Amend the
10 Scope of Practice for Expanded Function Dental Assistants”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
12 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
13 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
14 Whereas, the current licensing requirements for an expanded function dental assistant
15 require passage of a separate dental radiologic technique and safety examination, which is
16 the same examination required for licensure of dental radiographers; and
17 Whereas, this legislation eliminates the requirement that an expanded function dental
18 assistant must be separately licensed as a dental radiographer and instead provides for
19 exposing and processing radiographs under the assistant's scope of practice; and
20 Whereas, this legislation must be enacted immediately so that expanded function
21 dental assistants are not required to pay an additional license fee; and
22 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
23 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
24 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
25 therefore,'
26 Amend the bill by inserting before section 1 the following:
27 'Sec. 1. 32 MRSA §9854, sub-§3, ¶A, as amended by PL 2015, c. 429, §19, is
28 further amended to read:
29 A. A dentist, dental hygienist, expanded function dental assistant or dental
30 radiographer licensed under chapter 143;'
31 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
32 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
33 takes effect when approved.'
